epare for me great quantities of timber, for the house that I am to build will be extraordinarily great. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now look! I will supply the food for your servants, the woodcutters who cut down the trees: 20,000 cors}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of wheat, 20,000 cors of barley, 20,000 baths}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of wine, and 20,000 baths of oil.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that Hi\u697?ram the king of Tyre sent this written message to Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon: \u8220?Because Jehovah loves his people, he has made you their king.\u8221? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Hi\u697?ram then said: \u8220?May Jehovah the God of Israel be praised, who made the heavens and the earth, because he has given to King David a wise son, endowed with discretion and understanding, who will build a house for Jehovah and a house for his kingdom. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now I am sending a skilled craftsman, endowed with understanding, Hi\u697?ram-a\u697?bi, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?who is the son of a Dan\u697?ite woman but whose father was a man of Tyre; he has experience in working in gold, silver, copper, iron, stones, timbers, purple wool, blue thread, fine fabric, and crimson. He can do every sort of engraving and make any design he is given. He will work with your own skilled craftsmen and the skilled craftsmen of my lord David your father. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now let my lord send the wheat, barley, oil, and wine he has promised to his servants. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And we will cut down trees from Leb\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 non, as many as you need, and we will bring them to you as rafts by sea to Jop\u697?pa; and you will take them up to Jerusalem.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon then took a count of all the men who were foreign residents in the land of Israel, after the census taken by David his father, and there were found 153,600. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So he assigned 70,000 of them as common laborers,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  80,000 as stonecutters in the mountains, and 3,600 as overseers for putting the people to work.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 3\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon started to build the house of Jehovah in Jerusalem on Mount M}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ri\u697?ah, where Jehovah had appeared to his father David, in the place that David had prepared on the threshing floor of Or\u697?nan the Jeb\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 u}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 site. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He started to build on the second day of the second month, in the fourth year of his reign. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And the foundation that Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon laid for building the house of the true God was 60 cubits long and 20 cubits wide, according to the former measurement.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The porch in front was 20 cubits long, corresponding to the width of the house,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and its height was 120;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and he overlaid it inside with pure gold. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He paneled the great house with juniper wood, after which he covered it with fine gold, and then he decorated it with palm-tree figures and chains. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Further, he overlaid the house with beautiful precious stones; and the gold he used was gold from Pa}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 r}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 va\u697?im. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He covered the house, the rafters, the thresholds, its walls, and its doors with gold; and he engraved cherubs on the walls.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He now made the Most Holy compartment;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  its length matched the width of the house, 20 cubits, and its width was 20 cubits. He covered it with 600 talents}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of fine gold. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The weight of the gold for the nails was 50 shekels;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and he covered the roof chambers with gold.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then he made in the Most Holy compartment}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  two cherub sculptures, and he overlaid them with gold. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The overall length of the wings of the cherubs was 20 cubits; one wing of the first cherub was five cubits long and touched the wall of the house, and its other wing was five cubits long and touched one of the other cherub\u8217?s wings. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And one wing of the other cherub was five cubits long and touched the other wall of the house, and its other wing was five cubits long and touched one of the first cherub\u8217?s wings. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The wings of these cherubs were spread out 20 cubits; and they stood on their feet, and they faced inward.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He also made the curtain of blue thread, purple wool, crimson, and fine fabric, and incorporated cherub designs into it.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then he made two pillars at the front of the house, 35 cubits in length, and the capital on top of each pillar was five cubits. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And he made chains, like necklaces, and put them on the tops of the pillars, and he made 100 pomegranates and put them on the chains. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He set up the pillars in front of the temple, one to the right}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and one to the left;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  he named the one on the right Ja\u697?chin}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and the one on the left Bo\u697?az.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 4\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then he made the copper altar, 20 cubits long, 20 cubits wide, and 10 cubits high.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He made the Sea}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of cast metal. It was circular in shape, 10 cubits from brim to brim and 5 cubits high, and it took a measuring line 30 cubits long to encircle it. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And there were ornamental gourds under it, completely encircling it, ten to a cubit all around the Sea. The gourds were in two rows and were cast in one piece with it. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?It stood on 12 bulls, 3 facing north, 3 facing west, 3 facing south, and 3 facing east; and the Sea rested on them, and all their hindquarters were toward the center. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And its thickness was a handbreadth;}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and its brim was made like the brim of a cup, like a lily blossom. The reservoir could hold}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  3,000 bath measures.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Further, he made ten basins for washing and put five to the right and five to the left. They would rinse in them the things used for the burnt offering. But the Sea was for the priests for washing.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He then made ten lampstands of gold, as specified, and put them in the temple, five on the right and five on the left.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He also made ten tables and placed them in the temple, five on the right and five on the left; and he made 100 golden bowls.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then he made the courtyard of the priests and the great court}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and the doors for the court, and he overlaid their doors with copper. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And he placed the Sea on the right side, toward the southeast.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Hi\u697?ram also made the cans, the shovels, and the bowls.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 So Hi\u697?ram finished the work that he did for King Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon on the house of the true God: }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?the two pillars and the bowl-shaped capitals that were on top of the two pillars; the two networks to cover the two bowl-shaped capitals that were on top of the pillars; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?the 400 pomegranates for the two networks, two rows of pomegranates for each network, to cover the two bowl-shaped capitals that were on the pillars; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?the ten carriages}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and the ten basins on the carriages; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?the Sea and the 12 bulls beneath it; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?and the cans, the shovels, the forks, and all their utensils Hi\u697?ram-a\u697?biv made of polished copper for King Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon for the house of Jehovah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The king cast them in the district of the Jordan in the thick clay between Suc\u697?coth and Zer\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 dah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon made all these utensils in great quantities; the weight of the copper was not ascertained.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon made all the utensils for the house of the true God: the altar of gold; the tables with the showbread on them; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?the lampstands and their lamps of pure gold, to burn before the innermost room according to the requirements; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?and the blossoms, the lamps, and the snuffers,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of gold, the purest gold; }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?the extinguishers, the bowls, the cups, and the fire holders, of pure gold; and the entrance of the house, its inner doors for the Most Holy, and the doors of the house of the temple, of gold.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 5\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon completed all the work he had to do for the house of Jehovah. Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon then brought in the things that David his father had made holy, and he put the silver, the gold, and all the articles into the treasuries of the house of the true God. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that time Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon congregated the elders of Israel, all the heads of the tribes, the chieftains of the paternal houses of Israel. They came to Jerusalem to bring up the ark of the covenant of Jehovah from the City of David, that is, Zion. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?All the men of Israel assembled before the king at the festival}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  that is held in the seventh month.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So all the elders of Israel came, and the Levites lifted up the Ark. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?They brought up the Ark, the tent of meeting, and all the holy utensils that were in the tent. The priests and the Levites}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  brought them up. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?King Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon and the entire assembly of Israel who had been summoned to meet with him were before the Ark. So many sheep and cattle were being sacrificed that they could not be counted or numbered. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of Jehovah to its place, into the innermost room of the house, the Most Holy, underneath the wings of the cherubs. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Thus the wings of the cherubs were spread out over the place of the Ark, so that the cherubs covered over the Ark and its poles from above. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The poles were so long that the tips of the poles were visible from the Holy in front of the innermost room, but they were not visible from outside. And they are there to this day. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?There was nothing in the Ark but the two tablets that Moses placed in it at Hor\u697?eb, when Jehovah made a covenant with the people of Israel while they were coming out of Egypt.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When the priests came out from the holy place (for all the priests who were present had sanctified themselves, regardless of their divisions), }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?all the Levite singers who belonged to A\u697?saph, to He\u697?man, to J}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 du\u697?thun, and to their sons and their brothers were clothed in fine fabric, holding cymbals, stringed instruments, and harps; they were standing east of the altar, and along with them 120 priests were sounding the trumpets. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At the moment when the trumpeters and the singers were praising and thanking Jehovah in unison, and as the sound ascended from the trumpets, the cymbals, and the other musical instruments as they were praising Jehovah, \u8220?for he is good; his loyal love endures forever,\u8221? then the house, the house of Jehovah, was filled with a cloud. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The priests were not able to stand to minister because of the cloud, for the glory of Jehovah filled the house of the true God.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 6\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that time Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon said: \u8220?Jehovah said he would reside in the thick gloom. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now I have built a lofty house for you, an established place for you to dwell in forever.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then the king turned around and began to bless all the congregation of Israel while all the congregation of Israel stood. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?He said: \u8220?May Jehovah the God of Israel be praised, the one who by his own mouth promised my father David and by his own hands has given fulfillment, saying, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8216?From the day I brought my people out of the land of Egypt, I have not chosen a city out of all the tribes of Israel in which to build a house for my name to remain there, and I have not chosen a man to become leader over my people Israel. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But I have chosen Jerusalem for my name to remain there, and I have chosen David to be over my people Israel.\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And it was the heart\u8217?s desire of my father David to build a house for the name of Jehovah the God of Israel. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But Jehovah said to my father David, \u8216?It was your heart\u8217?s desire to build a house for my name, and you did well to desire this in your heart. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?However, you will not build the house, but your own son who is to be born to you}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  is the one who will build the house for my name.\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Jehovah has carried out the promise that he made, for I have succeeded my father David and I sit on the throne of Israel, just as Jehovah promised. I have also built the house for the name of Jehovah the God of Israel, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?and there I have placed the Ark containing the covenant that Jehovah made with the people of Israel.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then he stood before the altar of Jehovah in front of all the congregation of Israel, and he spread out his hands. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?(For Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon had made a platform of copper and put it in the middle of the court.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  It was five cubits}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  long, five cubits wide, and three cubits high; and he stood on it.) And he knelt down in front of all the congregation of Israel and spread his hands out to the heavens, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?and he said: \u8220?O Jehovah the God of Israel, there is no God like you in the heavens or on the earth, keeping the covenant and showing loyal love to your servants who are walking before you with all their heart. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?You have kept the promise that you made to your servant David my father. You made the promise with your own mouth, and this day you have fulfilled it with your own hand. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now, O Jehovah the God of Israel, keep the promise you made to your servant David my father when you said: \u8216?There will never fail to be a man of your line before me to sit on the throne of Israel, if only your sons will pay attention to their way by walking in my law, just as you have walked before me.\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now, O Jehovah the God of Israel, let the promise that you made to your servant David prove trustworthy.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?But will God really dwell with mankind on the earth? Look! The heavens, yes, the heaven of the heavens, cannot contain you; how much less, then, this house that I have built! }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now pay attention to the prayer of your servant and to his request for favor, O Jehovah my God, and listen to the cry for help and to the prayer that your servant is praying before you. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?May your eyes be open toward this house day and night, toward the place where you said that you would put your name, to listen to the prayer that your servant prays toward this place. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And listen to your servant\u8217?s pleas for help and to the pleas of your people Israel when they pray toward this place, and may you hear from your dwelling place, from the heavens; yes, may you hear and forgive.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?If a man sins against his fellow man and is made to take an oath}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and is brought under liability to the oath,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and while under the oath}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  he comes before your altar in this house, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 23}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?may you then hear from the heavens and act and judge your servants by paying back the wicked one and bringing what he did on his own head and by pronouncing the righteous one innocent}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and rewarding him according to his own righteousness.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 24}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?And if your people Israel are defeated by an enemy because they kept sinning against you, and they return and glorify your name and pray and beg for favor before you in this house, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 25}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?may you then hear from the heavens and forgive the sin of your people Israel and bring them back to the land that you gave to them and their forefathers.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 26}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?When the heavens are shut up and there is no rain because they kept sinning against you, and they pray toward this place and glorify your name and turn back from their sin because you humbled}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  them, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 27}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?may you then hear from the heavens and forgive the sin of your servants, of your people Israel, for you will instruct them about the good way in which they should walk; and bring rain on your land that you gave to your people as an inheritance.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 28}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?If a famine occurs in the land, or a pestilence, a scorching blight, mildew, swarming locusts, or voracious locusts}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  or if their enemies besiege them in any of the cities of the land}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  or if any other sort of plague or disease occurs, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 29}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?whatever prayer, whatever request for favor may be made by any man or by all your people Israel (for each one knows his own plague and his own pain) when they spread out their hands toward this house, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 30}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?then may you hear from the heavens, your dwelling place, and may you forgive; and reward each one according to all his ways, for you know his heart (you alone truly know the human heart), }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 31}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?so that they may fear you by walking in your ways all the days they live on the land that you gave to our forefathers.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 32}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?Also concerning the foreigner who is not part of your people Israel and who comes from a distant land because of your great name}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and your mighty hand and your outstretched arm, and he comes and prays toward this house, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 33}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?may you then listen from the heavens, your dwelling place, and do all that the foreigner asks of you, so that all the peoples of the earth may know your name and fear you, as your people Israel do, and may know that your name has been called on this house that I have built.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 34}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?If your people go to war against their enemies in the way that you send them and they pray to you in the direction of this city that you have chosen and toward the house that I have built for your name, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 35}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?then hear from the heavens their prayer and their request for favor and execute judgment for them.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 36}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?If they sin against you (for there is no man who does not sin), and you are furious with them and you abandon them to an enemy, and their captors carry them off captive to a land, far or near, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 37}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?and they come to their senses in the land where they were carried off captive, and they return to you and beg you for favor in the land where they are captives, saying, \u8216?We have sinned and done wrong; we have acted wickedly,\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 38}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?and they return to you with all their heart and all their soul}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  in the land of their captivity where they were carried off captive, and they pray in the direction of their land that you gave to their forefathers and the city that you have chosen and the house that I have built for your name, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 39}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?then hear from the heavens, your dwelling place, their prayer and their request for favor, and execute judgment for them and forgive your people who have sinned against you.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 40}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?Now, O my God, please, may your eyes be opened and your ears attentive to the prayer offered in}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  this place. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 41}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now go up, O Jehovah God, to your resting-place, you and the Ark of your strength. Let your priests, O Jehovah God, be clothed with salvation, and let your loyal ones rejoice in your goodness. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 42}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?O Jehovah God, do not reject}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  your anointed one. May you remember your loyal love to David your servant.\u8221?\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 7\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now as soon as Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon had finished praying, fire came down from the heavens and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices, and Jehovah\u8217?s glory filled the house. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The priests were unable to enter the house of Jehovah because Jehovah\u8217?s glory had filled the house of Jehovah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And all the people of Israel were looking on when the fire came down and the glory of Jehovah was upon the house, and they bowed low with their faces to the ground on the pavement and prostrated themselves and thanked Jehovah, \u8220?for he is good; his loyal love endures forever.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now the king and all the people offered sacrifices before Jehovah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?King Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon offered the sacrifice of 22,000 cattle and 120,000 sheep. Thus the king and all the people inaugurated the house of the true God. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?The priests were standing at their posts of duty, as were the Levites who had the instruments used to accompany the song to Jehovah. (King David had made these instruments for giving thanks to Jehovah\u8212?\u8220?for his loyal love endures forever\u8221?\u8212?when David would offer praise with them.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ) And the priests were loudly sounding the trumpets in front of them, while all the Israelites were standing.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon sanctified the middle of the courtyard that was before the house of Jehovah, for there he had to offer up the burnt offerings and the fat pieces of the communion sacrifices, because the copper altar that Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon had made could not contain the burnt sacrifices, the grain offerings, and the fat pieces. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that time Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon held the festival for seven days together with all Israel, a very great congregation from Le\u697?bo-ha\u697?math}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  down to the Wadi}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of Egypt. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But on the eighth day}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  they held a solemn assembly, because they had held the inauguration of the altar for seven days and the festival for seven days. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then on the 23rd day of the seventh month, he sent the people away to their homes rejoicing and feeling glad of heart over the goodness that Jehovah had shown to David and Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon and Israel his people.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Thus Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon finished the house of Jehovah and the house}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  of the king; and everything that came into Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon\u8217?s heart to do regarding the house of Jehovah and his own house he accomplished successfully. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Jehovah then appeared to Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon during the night and said to him: \u8220?I have heard your prayer, and I have chosen this place for myself as a house of sacrifice. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When I shut up the heavens and there is no rain and when I command the grasshoppers to devour the land and if I send a pestilence among my people, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?if my people on whom my name has been called humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn away from their evil ways, then I will hear from the heavens and forgive their sin and heal their land. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now my eyes will be open and my ears attentive to prayer at this place. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And now I have chosen and sanctified this house so that my name may be there permanently, and my eyes and my heart will always be there.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?And you, if you walk before me as your father David walked by doing everything I have commanded you, and you obey my regulations and my judgments, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?then I will establish the throne of your kingship, just as I made a covenant with your father David, saying, \u8216?There will never fail to be a man of your line ruling over Israel.\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But if you turn away and forsake my statutes and my commandments that I have put before you and you go and serve other gods and bow down to them, }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 20}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?I will uproot Israel from my land that I have given them, and this house that I have sanctified for my name I will cast out of my sight, and I will make it an object of scorn}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and a cause for ridicule among all the peoples. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 21}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And this house will become heaps of ruins. Everyone passing by it will stare in amazement and will say, \u8216?Why did Jehovah do that to this land and this house?\u8217? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 22}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Then they will say, \u8216?It was because they abandoned Jehovah the God of their forefathers, who had brought them out of the land of Egypt, and they embraced other gods and bowed down to them and served them. That is why he brought all this calamity on them.\u8217?\u8221?\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 8\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At the end of 20 years, during which Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon built the house of Jehovah and his own house,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon rebuilt the cities that Hi\u697?ram had given Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 o}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 mon and settled Israelites}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  there. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Furthermore, Sol\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5