cs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Now the spirit of God came upon A}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 za}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 ri\u697?ah the son of O\u697?ded. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So he went out to meet A\u697?sa and said to him: \u8220?Hear me, O A\u697?sa and all Judah and Benjamin! Jehovah is with you as long as you remain with him; and if you search for him, he will let himself be found by you, but if you abandon him, he will abandon you. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?For a long time}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  Israel had been without the true God, without a priest teaching, and without law. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But when in their distress they returned to Jehovah the God of Israel and searched for him, he let himself be found by them. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In those times no one could travel safely,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  for there was much unrest among all the inhabitants of the lands. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Nation was being crushed by nation and one city by another city, because God kept them in disorder with every sort of distress. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 7}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But you, be strong and do not become discouraged,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  for your activity will be rewarded.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 8}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?As soon as A\u697?sa heard these words and the prophecy of O\u697?ded the prophet, he took courage and removed the disgusting idols from all the land of Judah and Benjamin and from the cities that he had captured from the mountainous region of E\u697?phr}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 im, and he restored Jehovah\u8217?s altar that was before the porch of Jehovah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 9}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And he gathered together all Judah and Benjamin and the foreign residents with them from E\u697?phr}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 im and M}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 nas\u697?seh and Sim\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 e}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 on, for they had deserted to him from Israel in great number when they saw that Jehovah his God was with him. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 10}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So they were gathered together at Jerusalem in the third month of the 15th year of A\u697?sa\u8217?s reign. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 11}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?On that day they sacrificed to Jehovah from the spoil they had brought, 700 cattle and 7,000 sheep. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 12}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Furthermore, they entered into a covenant to search for Jehovah the God of their forefathers with all their heart and with all their soul.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 13}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Whoever would not search for Jehovah the God of Israel was to be put to death, whether small or great, man or woman. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 14}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?So they took an oath to Jehovah with a loud voice, with joyful shouting, and with the trumpets and horns. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 15}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And all Judah rejoiced over the oath, for they had taken the oath with all their heart and they eagerly sought him and he let himself be found by them, and Jehovah continued to give them rest on every side.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 16}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?A\u697?sa the king even removed Ma\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 cah his grandmother from her position as queen mother,}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  because she had made an obscene idol for the worship of the sacred pole.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  A\u697?sa cut down her obscene idol and pulverized it and burned it in the Kid\u697?ron Valley. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 17}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?But the high places were not removed from Israel. Nevertheless, A\u697?sa\u8217?s heart was complete}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  all his life.}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 18}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?And he brought the things that he and his father had made holy into the house of the true God\u8212?silver, gold, and various utensils. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 19}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?There was no war until the 35th year of A\u697?sa\u8217?s reign.\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf6\b Chapter }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f0\fs32\cf8\b 16\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql\fi576 {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?In the 36th year of the reign of A\u697?sa, King Ba\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 sha of Israel came up against Judah and began to build up}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  Ra\u697?mah to prevent anyone from going out or coming in to}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  King A\u697?sa of Judah. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 2}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?At that A\u697?sa brought out silver and gold from the treasuries of Jehovah\u8217?s house and the king\u8217?s house}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  and sent them to King Ben-ha\u697?dad of Syria, who was dwelling in Damascus, saying: }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 3}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?\u8220?There is a treaty}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  between me and you and between my father and your father. I am sending you silver and gold. Come, break your treaty}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  with King Ba\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 sha of Israel, so that he will withdraw from me.\u8221?\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 4}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?Ben-ha\u697?dad listened to King A\u697?sa and sent the chiefs of his armies against the cities of Israel, and they struck down I\u697?jon, Dan, A\u697?bel-ma\u697?im, and all the storage places of the cities of Naph\u697?t}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 li. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 5}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?When Ba\u697?}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf5 a}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 sha heard of it, he immediately quit building}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11  Ra\u697?mah and abandoned his work on it. }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf10 6}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf11 \u160?King A\u697?sa then took all Judah, and they carried off the stones and timbers of Ra